A Late Eocene age is indicated for the basal Turritella clays by the nannofossils Cyclicargolithus reticulatus, lsthmolithus recurvus, Chiasmolithus oamaruensis, and the foraminifer Acarinina collactea (Shafik & Idnurm, in preparation). A combination of magneto- and biostrati- graphy (Shafik & Idnurm, in preparation) suggests that the Turritella clays are within Chrons 16-18. lsthmolithus recurvus and Chiasmolithus oamaruensis appear at 37 Ma on GTS 2020
the presence of G. angulata and G. pseudomardi, which belong respectively to foraminiferal zones P3 and P4 (ages of 62.5 to 57 in GTS 2020)
